        {
            "ticket_id": 44946,
            "id": 12,
            "outcome": "Emailed User",
            "who": "Andrew Adams",
            "who_type": 1,
            "who_imgpath": "",
            "who_agentid": 4,
            "datetime": "2025-11-05T21:03:38.477",
            "actiondatecreated": "2025-11-05T21:03:41.43",
            "note": "Hello Guillaume,\r\n\r\nFollowing up through email after creating a Halo Ticket tied to your request early this morning about having issues in UAT related to feeding SWAP FRA via xml process server. \r\n\r\nProcess Server failed to consume xml because it was improperly named, this was corrected.You were getting file error rejects due to Unknown parameter SecTypCd. Solution was to correct to SecTypeCd.Last question you had was\r\n\r\nand I have responded to you with the following;\r\n\r\nHaving not been previously privy to how you all previously imported the Trades and Securities when you were doing the Sophis Migration with how you built the various Trades, I don't have a direct shell to reference. \r\n \r\nWould need to either review documentation or would likely refer to one of the older xml's that was used to import the Swaps previously. But as FRA lacks the additional legs, it's likely it'll require a number of adjustments. \r\n\r\nIf the extant prior templates you all used are not sufficient to this task, I'm sure we can take a look and see what is the cause and assist with troubleshooting. At this time I will be proceeding with closing this ticket as we've addressed your various concerns tied to this.",
